2️⃣ File Details
index.html – Home Page

Sections:

Header / Navigation (responsive)

Hero Section (headline, subheadline, CTA buttons)

Trust Strip (icon + text for credibility)

Featured Firms Preview (cards dynamically loaded via firms.js)

Latest Blog Preview (cards dynamically loaded via blog.js)

Footer (links + copyright)

Enhancements:

Gradient hero background

Buttons: primary & outline

Responsive & mobile-first

firms.html – Prop Firms Listing

Sections:

Search / Filter form (Capital, Profit Split)

Full grid of firm cards (firm-grid) loaded dynamically via firms.js

Footer

JS functionality (firms.js):

Fetch firms.json

Render cards dynamically

Filter firms on form submit

Lazy-load logos for faster performance

compare.html – Compare Firms

Sections:

Two dropdowns to select firms (firmA, firmB)

Dynamic comparison table (compare-table)

Footer

JS functionality (compare.js):

Fetch firms.json

Populate dropdowns

Render comparison table dynamically

Highlights metrics visually

Handles responsive layout

blog.html – Blog Listing

Sections:

Blog cards container (blog-grid)

Footer

JS functionality (blog.js):

Fetch blogs.json

Render blog cards dynamically

Each card: title, excerpt, “Read More” link

blog-post.html – Single Blog Post (Template)

Loads blog content dynamically or statically

Uses query string slug (?slug=...) to identify post

about.html – Company / Trust Page

Contains:

Company story

Certifications, partnerships, and team (optional)

Contact CTA

Optional JS for small interactions

3️⃣ CSS Files

base.css → resets, default body, typography, links

layout.css → grid/flex containers, spacing utilities

components.css → reusable components like:

.btn, .card, .compare-table, .trust-item

pages.css → page-specific styling:

Hero section

Featured firms section

Compare preview

Blog preview

Trust strip and footer

Responsive adjustments

4️⃣ JS Files

main.js

Mobile nav toggle

Smooth scroll for internal links

Handles responsive nav on resize

firms.js

Fetch and render firms.json

Filter firms by capital/profit split

Lazy-load logos

compare.js

Populate two dropdowns from firms.json

Render comparison table

Highlights best metrics

blog.js

Fetch and render blogs.json

Create blog cards dynamically

Root Folder structure: 

FPT_new/
├── index.html           # Home page – hero, trust, featured firms, blog preview, footer
├── firms.html           # Full list of prop firms with filtering
├── compare.html         # Compare two prop firms dynamically
├── blog.html            # Blog listing page
├── blog-post.html       # Single blog post template
├── about.html           # About / trust / company info
│
├── assets/
│   ├── css/
│   │   ├── base.css       # Reset, global styles
│   │   ├── layout.css     # Grid, flex, spacing, container layout
│   │   ├── components.css # Reusable components (buttons, cards, tables)
│   │   └── pages.css      # Page-specific styling (hero, firms, compare, blog, trust)
│   ├── js/
│   │   ├── main.js        # Global JS: mobile menu toggle, smooth scroll
│   │   ├── firms.js       # Load prop firms from JSON, render cards, filter
│   │   ├── compare.js     # Dynamic firm comparison table
│   │   └── blog.js        # Load blog posts dynamically from JSON
│   └── images/
│       ├── logos/         # Prop firm logos (webp/png)
│       └── icons/         # SVG icons for trust/features
│
└── data/
    ├── firms.json         # Prop firm dataset (id, name, capital, profit split, payout, logo)
    └── blogs.json         # Blog dataset (slug, title, excerpt, date)

